: He rules. Also, he posted his [http://groups.google.com/groups?selm=vafr8g3wllt.fsf%40lucy.cs.uni-dortmund.de&output=gplain ~/.viper] file to comp.emacs the other day.

An archive of his home page can be found [http://web.archive.org/web/20010516025950/ls6-www.cs.uni-dortmund.de/~grossjoh/ in the big archive]. There's also [http://www.is.informatik.uni-duisburg.de/staff/kai.html a more formal web page].

He uses Emacs.

One of the things you'll find there is TrampMode (formerly rcp.el).

Also, he's written the IndentationTutorial, a precursor to the GnusTutorial, and others.

He also did nnir.el.

